"{\"uid\": \"si.com-high-school-oregon-oregon-high-school-athletes-competing-in-2024-paris-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"The 2024 Paris Summer Olympics are officially underway as the best athletes in the world gather in France looking for their shot at Olympic glory.  Eight athletes fromOregonwill compete for Team USA at the Olympics and Paralympics.  For most of these athletes, spending time at anOregon high schoolwas part of their hard-fought journey to the 2024 Paris Olympics.  Here is a look at the former Oregon high school athletes in the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics.  *Taylor Averill was born in Beaverton but attended high school in California atBranham High School.  **Cameron Brink was a standout at Stanford and was recently selected No. 2 overall by the Los Angeles Sparks in the 2024 WNBA Draft. She qualified for the 2024 Olympics but will not be able to participate after tearing her ACL in June.  The 2024 Paralympics will take place August 28 through September 8 in Paris.  Below are the two Team USA athletes representing Oregon at the Paralympics in France this summer:  *Dennis Connors was born in Beaverton but there is no record of him attending high school in Oregon.  You can find more of the latest Olympic coverage onSBLive.  To get live updates on your phone - as well as follow your favorite high school teams and top games - you can download the SBLive Sports app:  Download iPhone App|Download Android App  -- Sam Brown | sam@scorebooklive.com |@sblivesports  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Sam Brown covers high school sports as well as NCAA football and basketball. Sam began his professional career as a high school sports reporter for The Tennessean in Nashville where he covered boys and girls prep sports full-time and helped cover Vanderbilt football, Tennessee Titans football and Nashville Predators hockey. He graduated from Middle Tennessee State University with a double major in journalism and 